I mainly purchased this add-on to support the developer. The app itself, Termux, is an amazing piece of software. Dunno what I'd do without it.  Now, I figured I'd write a short review for this add-on anyway, so here goes!  The ability to choose hex values, like some/most Linux terminal emulators, would be amazing. That said, the developer has alleviated this somewhat by adding a lot of presets to choose from. I hope they add this feature eventually.  The same applies to the fonts. The ability to upload your own to the emulator would be great, but the developer has added a good choice of fonts and has included his email address in case you want to send suggestions.
replyContent: After installing a color theme, you can edit hex values by editing the file ~/.termux/colors.properties - then run termux-reload-settings to have them take effect!

content: Lets you choose between some fonts and some preset colors. Still needs the ability to make custom color themes and to set font size.
replyContent:
- Make a custom color theme by editing $HOME/.termux/colors.properties (start with something like https://gist.github.com/fornwall/9695f0eae5685f484451). Run termux-reload-settings after editing the file to have it take effect.

- Set font size by pinch zooming.

replyContent:
You can change font size by pinch zooming (or by double tapping on the terminal and pulling a finger down or up).

User defined customization is already possible - put something like https://gist.github.com/fornwall/9695f0eae5685f484451 in $HOME/.termux/colors.properties and call termux-reload-settings.

Great extension for great app! it would be nice if user defined fonts, colors (not entire schemes, but specific components like bg) get supported in next releases.
replyContent:
For user defined fonts and colors:

- Change font by putting a font file in $HOME/.termux/font.ttf.

- Change colors by editing $HOME/.termux/colors.properties (start with something like https://gist.github.com/fornwall/9695f0eae5685f484451).

Run termux-reload-settings after changing any of the above files.
